{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"some-rockable-bluejay","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Problem\nIn a consumer repo (rebar installed, no rebar docs/ tree), every coaching deep-link in review-plan output points to a nonexistent local file, so the documented 'follow the link to understand the criterion you failed' affordance is dead out of the box.\n\n## Root cause (confirmed against installed v0.10.0)\nconfig.plan_review_docs_url() defaults to (repo_root()/'docs'/'plan-review-criteria-guide.md').as_uri() = file://<consumer-repo>/docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md when REBAR_DOCS_URL is unset. orchestrator coaching builds guide_url from that base. src/rebar/config.py:67-74; orchestrator ~line 578. (The 'rebar explain' COMMAND was separately fixed in c2bfbe217 by packaging guides; the deep-link URL default was not.)\n\n## Fix\nDefault plan_review_docs_url to a canonical published URL (the upstream hosted docs for the criteria guide) rather than a consumer-repo file:// path, still overridable by REBAR_DOCS_URL. Links then resolve for consumers by default.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- With REBAR_DOCS_URL unset and cwd a consumer repo (no docs/ tree), plan_review_docs_url() returns a canonical http(s) URL, not a file:// path under the consumer repo.\n- REBAR_DOCS_URL still overrides.\n- A unit test asserts the default is a canonical hosted URL (not file://); asserting the old file:// default would FAIL.\n\n## Verification\npytest asserting the default scheme is http(s) and anchors resolve as <url>#<criterion-id>.","id":"c7e3-dd16-f0a8-43aa","parent_id":"56c0-1d2f-f39c-4ac1","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"plan-review coaching deep-links resolve to a file:// path in the consuming repo (dead for consumers)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784776527067355001,"uuid":"ae776fb3-eb2d-40ef-9d96-97050e705fcf"}